rty data exposure (Nov–Dec) - Year-end roundups warn 2025 data breaches were unusually large and impactful (Dec retrospectives) - China-nexus groups among first to weaponize React2Shell hours after disclosure (Dec) - CISA adds Apple WebKit zero-day to its catalog and issues mitigation guidance (Dec mid-Dec) - Fastly, Cloudflare and other CDN/WAF vendors release virtual patches and mitigations for React2Shell (Dec) - Microsoft warns of multiple Exchange/Office vulnerabilities patched in December (Patch Tuesday) - Security firms report new AI-powered phishing kits and MFA-bypass toolkits (Dec) - Unusual scanning and credential stuffing hits Cisco SSL VPNs and other SSL portals (Nov–Dec) - Weekly product/security roundups announce new infosec tools and services (mid-Dec) - Europol and national law enforcement disrupt crypto-fraud and fake-investment networks (Nov–Dec) - Local police operations in India net dozens of suspects in cyber-fraud rings (Dec) - React2Shell public exploit code prompts emergency responses from cloud providers and universities (Dec) - Default Next.js/React Server Component deployments flagged as vulnerable to RCE (Dec) - Security teams push virtual patches after widespread RSC exploit attempts (Dec) - Dark-web leak sites continue double-extortion postings as extortion tactics shift (Nov–Dec) - Corporations face class actions and lawsuits after November data exposures (Under Armour suits reported) - Industry reports note a plateau in volume but growth in sophistication of ransomware tactics (Nov reports) - CISA and partners issue multiple malware analysis briefs and alerts through December (Dec) - Public exploit availability leads to mass scanning and opportunistic compromises (Dec) - Threat actors increasingly target cloud telemetry/analytics providers in supply-chain smishing attacks (Nov) - Misconfigured cloud storage and vendor data exposures continue to cause mass leaks in November (Nov roundups) - Global security vendors announce AI-driven d